result.execSummary:
The defendant Lance H. Lecher was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Lance H. Lecher is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Lance H. Lecher was found guilty of OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Lance H. Lecher was found guilty of Possess w/Intent-THC (<=200 grams) [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
D.A. John Snider appeared for the state.
Defendant appeared, in custody, with Atty. Dalkert.
Plea quest. & waiver of rights form filed with the Court.
The defendant enters pleas of no contest to Counts 1 and 3 of the information.  Pleas accepted by the Court after rights were explained and the defendant was found guilty as to Counts 1 and 3.  Count 2 is dismissed; Counts 4 and 5 are dismissed and read-in.
The parties stipulate that a factual basis exists to accept the pleas. Victims were notified, per D.A.
As to Count 1:  The Court orders a fine of $350.00 plus costs (total: $1421.50) This amount must be paid during the period of extended supervision in Count 3.  The defendant is ordered to serve 6 months in jail, concurrent with Wood Co. case 03 CF 349.  1 year revocation of operating privileges, AODA and DSP. No IID ordered.
As to Count 3:  The Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a period of 3 years, 6 months.
ITOC - 18 months
Term of EXS - 2 years
Sentence is concurrent with Count 1 and with also with Wood County case 03 CF 349.
Defendant has credit of 97 days on each count. 
Defendant is eligible for substance abuse and earned release.
Conditions of EXS will be determined by the agent.
Appeal rights, WEDS form, voter ineligibility and firearms restrictions were provided.
Cell phone and vehicle seized may be retrieved by family members after the statutory time period.
